Description:
    Generates a simple Ruby class with the given NAME

Example:
    `bin/rails generate example Name`

    This will create:
        app/models/name.rb
        test/models/name_test.rb

    `bin/rails generate example Point x y`

    This will create these files and add x and y attr_accessor:
        app/models/name.rb
        test/models/name_test.rb

    `bin/rails generate example Point x y --no-active-model`

    This will create these files, add x and y attr_accessor, but skip the ActiveModel include:
        app/models/name.rb